post_text: Tomorrow is the first day of school for the 2020-2021 school year! We are so excited to welcome everyone back. For those students learning in person, parents, please ensure you drop off your child/children in the morning and pick your child/children up in the afternoon at the times indicated in Genesis. For those students learning remotely, please be sure to log into your homeroom at 8:20 am. Thank you for your anticpated cooperation and we look forward to a successful school year. #NES #weareNetcongschool #Netcongstrong

post_text: At its special meeting last night, the Netcong Board of Education approved an updated school calendar pushing the start of the school year back to Thursday, September 3, 2020. September 1, 2020, and September 2, 2020, will now be utilized as professional development days for our staff as they prepare for both in-person and virtual learning. A copy of the updated calendar is attached for your reference. https://app.luminpdf.com/viewer/5f2c1462388a79001aa52642

OLIVE ESTÁ OFRECIENDO PRUEBAS FÍSICAS Y VACUNAS GRATUITAS PARA NIÑOS QUE SON RESIDENTES DE MOUNT OLIVE, NETCONG, MOUNT ARLINGTON, DOVER, WHARTON Y MINE HILL QUE NO TIENEN SEGURO DE SALUD O QUE TIENEN EL PROGRAMA NJ FAMILY CARE A. UN PEDIATRA CON LICENCIA REALIZARÁ LAS PRUEBAS FÍSICAS Y LA ACTUALIZACIÓN DE VACUNAS.

NO SE PERMITIRÁ ENTRADA SIN UNA CITA.

KINDERGARTEN.

Contacte a Helen Giles, RN al 973-691-0900 x7353

o por correo electrónico: hgiles@mtolivetwp.org

post_text:
The Netcong School District has been approved to serve breakfast and lunch for all students and their siblings in the home, 18 years of age and younger, until August 31, 2020. Meals will be available for pick up on Mondays and Thursdays from 9:00 am - 11:00 am at the school. Three days of meals for breakfast and lunch will be available on Mondays and two days of meals for breakfast and lunch will be available on Thursdays.

If you have any questions, please feel free to contact the main office. Thank you.

post_text: Calling all Netcong parents....the PTA officers are stepping down as most of them have students who are graduating 8th grade and moving on to high school. At this time, the PTA is in need of a new slate of officers to lead the Netcong School PTA for the 2020-2021 school year. If you are interested in holding a position as an officer in next year's PTA, please contact Dawn Fralley at netcongpta@netcongschool.org. If there are no interested parties to serve as officers of the PTA Executive Board, the Netcong School District will not have a PTA for the 2020-2021 school year. Thank you in advance to anyone who is willing and able to take on a role as an officer in the PTA.
text: Calling all Netcong parents....the PTA officers are stepping down as most of them have students who are graduating 8th grade and moving on to high school. At this time, the PTA is in need of a new slate of officers to lead the Netcong School PTA for the 2020-2021 school year. If you are interested in holding a position as an officer in next year's PTA, please contact Dawn Fralley at netcongpta@netcongschool.org. If there are no interested parties to serve as officers of the PTA Executive Board, the Netcong School District will not have a PTA for the 2020-2021 school year. Thank you in advance to anyone who is willing and able to take on a role as an officer in the PTA.

post_text: Due to the Memorial Day holiday on Monday, May 25, 2020, the Netcong School District will be closed. As a result of the holiday, meals will not be distributed on Monday, May 25, 2020. Those needing meals next week will be able to pick up meals on Tuesday, May 26, 2020 between 9:00 am - 11:00 am and Thursday, May 28, 2020 between 9:00 am - 11:00 am. Regular Monday and Thursday meal pick up will resume on Monday, June 1, 2020, and will continue through Monday, June 15, 2020, the last day of school for the 2019-2020 school year. Stay safe and well.
text: Due to the Memorial Day holiday on Monday, May 25, 2020, the Netcong School District will be closed. As a result of the holiday, meals will not be distributed on Monday, May 25, 2020. Those needing meals next week will be able to pick up meals on Tuesday, May 26, 2020 between 9:00 am - 11:00 am and Thursday, May 28, 2020 between 9:00 am - 11:00 am. Regular Monday and Thursday meal pick up will resume on Monday, June 1, 2020, and will continue through Monday, June 15, 2020, the last day of school for the 2019-2020 school year. Stay safe and well.

post_text: La Despensa de Alimentos de Netcong, que se encuentra enfrente del Netcong Borough Hall en la 23 Maple Ave, ahora ha extendido su horario de 9 a.m. a 1 p.m. todos los martes y jueves. La despensa también estará abierta el viernes de las 5 p.m. hasta las 7 p.m. exclusivamente para familias que no pueden pasar a buscar alimentos los martes o jueves. La despensa está disponible para cualquier persona que necesite asistencia durante este momento difícil, y ahora también ofrece productos congelados como pollo, carne y leche cuando estén disponibles.
text: La Despensa de Alimentos de Netcong, que se encuentra enfrente del Netcong Borough Hall en la 23 Maple Ave, ahora ha extendido su horario de 9 a.m. a 1 p.m. todos los martes y jueves. La despensa también estará abierta el viernes de las 5 p.m. hasta las 7 p.m. exclusivamente para familias que no pueden pasar a buscar alimentos los martes o jueves. La despensa está disponible para cualquier persona que necesite asistencia durante este momento difícil, y ahora también ofrece productos congelados como pollo, carne y leche cuando estén disponibles.

post_text: The Netcong Food Bank, which is located in front of the Netcong Borough Hall at 23 Maple Ave, has now extended its hours from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. every Tuesday and Thursday. Additionally, the Netcong Food Bank will also be open on Friday and from 5 p.m. to 7 p.m. exclusively for families who cannot visit the food bank on Tuesday or Thursday. The Netcong Food Bank is open to anyone, and now offers perishable products, such as chicken, meat, and milk when available.
text: The Netcong Food Bank, which is located in front of the Netcong Borough Hall at 23 Maple Ave, has now extended its hours from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. every Tuesday and Thursday. Additionally, the Netcong Food Bank will also be open on Friday and from 5 p.m. to 7 p.m. exclusively for families who cannot visit the food bank on Tuesday or Thursday. The Netcong Food Bank is open to anyone, and now offers perishable products, such as chicken, meat, and milk when available.

post_text:
The Lenape Valley Football & Cheer program is providing free virtual kids' workout videos.

Over the next 6 weeks, a new playlist will be posted on YouTube (starting Monday, May 18th)
These are curated and demonstrated by Holly Nikituk, a certified youth sports trainer
Each playlist will have a description of each exercise for parents to assist with form, pace, and safety
This is suitable for elementary and middle school-age kids – boys and girls
You don’t need to play football or cheer to participate - we encourage you to be your best!
Links to the videos will be available through the Lenape Valley Football & Cheer program website at www.lvpatriots.com (posted Mondays).

If you are interested in football or cheer for the upcoming season, please register while you’re on the site. No payments until at least July 1. Stay safe, be healthy!

post_text:
Unfortunately due to the threat of rain, with the possibility of thunder, lightning, and high winds, the parade scheduled for today is canceled. Weather permitting, the parade is rescheduled for Monday, April 20th and will begin at approximately 12 noon. We are disappointed that this could not happen today but we must ensure the safety of all participants.

We hope that you have a safe, happy, healthy, and restful spring break. We miss you all. Stay safe and well.

#NES #weareNetcongschool #Netcongstrong
text:
Unfortunately due to the threat of rain, with the possibility of thunder, lightning, and high winds, the parade scheduled for today is canceled. Weather permitting, the parade is rescheduled for Monday, April 20th and will begin at approximately 12 noon. We are disappointed that this could not happen today but we must ensure the safety of all participants.

We hope that you have a safe, happy, healthy, and restful spring break. We miss you all. Stay safe and well.

#NES #weareNetcongschool #Netcongstrong

The Great PIZZA PARTY RAFFLE COMPETITION Continues….

The Netcong Education Foundation’s Great Pizza Party raffle competition is going strong!

There is still time to help your class win. Just pick up a book of raffle tickets in the main office, sell them, return the money and sold tickets, and your ticket sales will count towards your class total. And remember, for every book of 10 raffle tickets you sell, your name is placed in a drawing to win a chrome book !!!!!

Current leaders in the pizza party class war are:

First place.............Ms. Garcia’s 2nd grade class

Second place......Mrs. Kirkland’s Preschool class

Current leader for most Raffle books sold:

First place..... Kayla Salinas

Remember to get your sold raffle books in by Friday, February 8th and be eligible to win a pair of tickets to Liberty Science Center!

Who wants pizza? Help sell those raffle tickets for pizza and a chance to win a chrome book!!!!

A big thank you to all those who have participated so far. GREAT JOB

Stay tuned to see who will win!!!

Attention Netcong Families!!! LVRHS invited parents and community members to the following presentation.

From LVRHS: Please join us Monday, January 20th, 2020 at 7:00pm in the Lenape Valley Auditorium as we welcome back Timothy Shoemaker, a potent and powerful keynote speaker who last year delivered an impactful presentation about the dangers of Vaping. This year Timothy is back to share with our students, staff and parents a motivational assembly designed to help students who are struggling to cope with stress and anxiety. Timothy’s “Hero” presentation provides parents with helpful strategies when dealing with a child who may be struggling with the pressure and worries of life. For more information please visit http://timothyshoemaker.com/hero/.

post_text:
The Netcong Board of Education has an open Trustee position due to the resignation of Mr. Timothy Domick. The Board wants to thank Mr. Domick for his many years of dedication and service to the Netcong School community.

The Netcong Board of Education will be accepting letters of interest for any person wishing to fill the vacancy on the Board of Education. All letters must be received no later than 4:00 p.m. on February 21, 2020. The Board will interview all interested candidates at its regularly scheduled meeting on February 25, 2020. All letters of interest should be submitted to Mr. Paul Stabile, Board Secretary, via email at pstabile@netcongschool.org.

The successful candidate will not be seated until they have passed the required Office of Student Protection fingerprint and background check mandated by law. The successful candidate must submit fingerprint and background checks within 30 days of being selected as a successful candidate.
text:
The Netcong Board of Education has an open Trustee position due to the resignation of Mr. Timothy Domick. The Board wants to thank Mr. Domick for his many years of dedication and service to the Netcong School community.

The Netcong Board of Education will be accepting letters of interest for any person wishing to fill the vacancy on the Board of Education. All letters must be received no later than 4:00 p.m. on February 21, 2020. The Board will interview all interested candidates at its regularly scheduled meeting on February 25, 2020. All letters of interest should be submitted to Mr. Paul Stabile, Board Secretary, via email at pstabile@netcongschool.org.

The successful candidate will not be seated until they have passed the required Office of Student Protection fingerprint and background check mandated by law. The successful candidate must submit fingerprint and background checks within 30 days of being selected as a successful candidate.

The Netcong Board of Education has an open trustee position. Last evening, Mr. Timothy Domick tendered his resignation from the Netcong Board of Education effective immediately. The Board wants to thank Mr. Domick for his many years of dedication and service to the Netcong School community.

The Netcong Board of Education will be accepting letters of interest for any person wishing to fill the vacancy on the Board of Education. All letters must be received no later than 4pm on January 10, 2020. The Board will interview all interested candidates at its regularly scheduled meeting on January 14, 2020. All letters of interest should be submitted to Mr. Paul Stabile, Board Secretary, via email at pstabile@netcongschool.org.

The successful candidate will not be seated until they have passed the required fingerprint and background check mandated by law. The successful candidate must submit to the fingerprint and background checks within 30 days of being selected as a successful candidate.

post_text: Donations are needed!!!! The NEF is sponsoring a collection drive and is collecting hats, gloves, scarves, blankets, socks, and gift cards for those less fortunate. Volunteers are needed to help package items on January 11th at 10am at the school. All participants that volunteer their time at the wrapping event will be entered into a raffle to win 4 Disney Park Hopper Passes. The winning ticket will be drawn at the conclusion of the event. To volunteer your time at this event, please sign up at https://www.allforgood.org/projects/bJ7AYBQ9 #NES #weareNetcongschool #NetcongEducationalFoundation

post_text:
Good evening.
Due to potentially hazardous conditions tomorrow morning, the Netcong Elementary School will operate on a delayed opening schedule on Tuesday, December 17, 2019.
Students in grades PK-8 may begin reporting to school at 9:30 am when they can go to their inclement weather locations. Homeroom and first period will begin at 9:45 am.
For students in our PSD program, class will run from 9:45am - 12:00pm.
Students who participate in our breakfast program may report to school at 9:15 am to eat breakfast.
Before Care is canceled.
Have a good night.

post_text: Due to the impending inclement weather, all after school activities at Netcong Elementary School are cancelled on 12/16/19. After Care will remain in session until all students are picked up by a parent or guardian. Have a good evening and please be safe.
